SIMPLE: strainer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strainer
<hw>Strain"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
strains.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That through which any liquid is passed for
purification or to separate it from solid matter; anything, as a screen
or a cloth, used to strain a liquid; a device of the character of a
sieve or of a filter; specifically, an openwork or perforated screen, as
for the end of the suction pipe of a pump, to prevent large solid bodies
from entering with a liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Straining</ent>⟦br⟧
